snippet.textDisplay: This style of coffee didn't originate in South Korea. An actor from there tried it in Macau and he brought it back home. He called it Dalgona coffee because it reminded him of dalgona, which is some dessert or candy from South Korea, I think. Anyway, this coffee actually originates from Pakistan and India. It's called "whipped coffee." We've been making our coffee like this for generations. I'm glad that people are enjoying it, but a little sad that they think it came from SK.
